column5: Took a drive up to the cottage near Buckhorn today  Gannon Narrows open as far as the eye can see either side of the bridge in the channel.  Crazy circular area, about 100 ft in diameter, of open water on the south side of the Chemong causeway near the middle.  Looks like open water, or else it's sitting on the surface.  What's this all about?
like crop circles.........aliens............shhhh they are watching all of us.   Art
so....anybody know what the circular open water is on Chemong?  underwater spring?
I was in Bridgenorth for a haircut this morning and meant to go have a look and completely forgot about it.  It's a bugger getting old(er)
Pretty sure its just water on top of the ice, it has been a pretty big puddle but today I noticed it was about half the size.

I was in Bridgenorth for a haircut this morning and meant to go have a look and completely forgot about it.  It's a bugger getting old(er) Welcome to the club my friend...Like Jack used to say..."It's me age don't you know"...

That is water over the ice, will freeze tonight with minus 9 temps, seen what you were posting about on Saturday myself, sure did look hopeful though, need it to melt from the shoreline, and then some big winds to break it up
